{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"12015a9d-5fd9-4321-ba54-991dca598f35","agentId":"a7f604c3f098f41dc","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"\nKata: Conway's Game of Life with infinite grid (sparse representation).\n\nRules:\n1. Underpopulation: live cell with < 2 live neighbors dies\n2. Survival: live cell with 2 or 3 live neighbors lives on\n3. Overpopulation: live cell with > 3 live neighbors dies\n4. Reproduction: dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive\n\nConstraints:\n- Grid is infinite in all directions (positive and negative x/y)\n- Only track living cells (sparse representation)\n- Cells identified by coordinates (x, y)\n- A \"generation\" transforms current state to next state\n\nExamples from the spec:\n- Single cell dies (underpopulation, 0 neighbors)\n- Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation, each has 1 neighbor)\n- Cell with 2 neighbors survives\n- Cell with 3 neighbors survives\n- Cell with 4 neighbors dies (overpopulation)\n- Dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)\n- Block pattern (still life) stays unchanged\n- Blinker pattern oscillates\n- Empty grid stays empty\n\nFiles:\n- Test file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts\n- Implementation file: src/game-of-life.ts\n\nThe function signature should be: nextGeneration(liveCells: [number, number][]): [number, number][]\n\nCreate the test file with it.todo() entries. Also create the minimal implementation file that just exports the function stub.\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously.\n"},"uuid":"fe880cb5-89ae-4a54-92de-17ad19573af4","timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:17:03.105Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-11_10-16-25_game-of-life-example-mapping_v4.2-conservative_opus-4-6-portkey","sessionId":"8f70547f-ff62-4b39-b8f4-6df157a7cb18","version":"2.1.107","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"sharded-gathering-pebble"}
